by Soveiniesberg » Sat Apr 09, 2022 6:25 pm

Inspiratus wrote:Monkeys 829 - 821 attend the funerals of Monkeys 840 to 830. While their caskets were being lowered to the ground, red rays shined out from a point between the graves, and air seemed to swirl around the nexus. The tips of grass swayed toward it, then flew, then came leaves and twigs and hats and small trinkets and more as the gathered monkeys panicked at this unnatural state of events. The rays centered at an orb of light, perhaps some sort of power, that seemed to expand, and with it the surroundings seem to increase in heat, as if some reaction, some process unrecognizable by sight and knowledge is creating an alien product that will be dispersed to the poor monkeys. The monkeys moved away, farther and farther, until the sphere, at its zenith when it has engulfed the hill the ceremony was on, shrank suddenly and a loud noise reverberated throughout the graveyard. The monkeys, seemingly unharmed, looked up and saw a thing.

The thing was familiar for all monkeys, for it had attributes that the monkeys seen in the reflections of themselves. It had hands, it had two legs, it had two arms, it had the shape of a monkey, albeit bigger and stretched out. But its face. Its face. It was not a hairy face, but a bare one; the nose was not flat, but jutted out of the face to a point and returned at a steep angle; the eyes were round, and with ivory around it, with a few hairs surrounding the boundary between eye and pale skin; and what hair there is clumped together around the top, making a mound noticeably compact, and yet airy.

The being looked down, and suddenly came down, without use of its upper or lower limbs. It was still, and seemingly rose up and descended among the monkeys without lifting a finger. The monkeys cowered amongst themselves, wondering who this strange being from the shining globe was and if it was something to fear.

"I am," began the being, looking down, "not a god. But I am in the servitude of essentially gods."

"I know the truth of this peculiar universe. I know its uselessness amongst other universes. I know that the beings of old, coming from dimensions operating on strange rules, treat this as a mere game; not a game to focus on, but a game to look, to laugh, to let suffering upon suffering occur for some fleeting enjoyment, before they leave to focus on something else. I know the horrors of this, for I am its caretaker. I am forced to allow this mad suffering, this genocide of innocents beings, not out of duty, but because I am a puppet to their desire."

"And as I am a puppet, I am forced to inflict this tragic pain upon you fools. One of these beings, a swelling idiot whose eye looks upon this universe with glee, has volunteered itself in a rare act of industry to count the number of monkeys deceased by their hands. And it has deemed it to be excessive. It believes that too many monkeys have died according to their alien rules, and intends to bring back a thousand to kill. And it will be the already deceased that will be killed again, with their memories of their deaths scarred within their minds for the being's own amusement."

"I am sorry, for your pain will continue."

With that, the puppet raised its arms, and screamed, as out from the mouths came monkey after monkey, all rising into the air before tumbling down the hill. Monkeys with scars, with bruises, with signs of their previous state of existence, and all with eyes displaying horror. They screamed as they fell, and cried out for mercy, for a return to their nonexistence. Some tried to make the journey by themselves with deep cuts to their throats and gut, but it only seemed to add mor pain. The original monkeys fled, and cried out the warnings of eldritch things looking upon them like ants to be smashed in. One monkey, not looking, was run over, its cry silenced by the noise of the car.

Monkey 1950 died in a car accident.
